descriptionMd:
*on our way (home)* is an exercise in collective trust and exchange to map out the traces we live in a city. 
&nbsp;
Our phones carry our whole lives in data: where we've been, what we're interested in, and more. We know how this data can be weaponized against us by governments and institutions or shared as an intimate offering with our closest friends. 
&nbsp;
This piece plays with the murky middle, inviting us to share these intimate pieces of data with strangers.
&nbsp;
Inspired by Félix González-Torres’ [Candy Works](https://www.felixgonzalez-torresfoundation.org/works/c/candy-works), each installation features a seemingly endless supply of tickets that visitors are invited to take to begin their participation. Each ticket contains a QR code linking to the piece’s mobile app. The app invites visitors to grant access to their location as they return from the exhibition. Each participant’s trail slowly accumulates until they arrive home. At that point, it is added to the screen installation that continuously animates through each trail. 
&nbsp;
After submitting a trail, the app turns into a compass that directs back to the source installation. To see one’s own submitted trail, one must return to where they first encountered the piece. While our data economies encourage short attention spans and moving on to the latest trend, this piece invites us to not only contend with the data we produce but also slow down and appreciate seeing things again with fresh eyes.
